In this article, it is stated that President Obama had separate phone conversations with British Prime Minister David Cameron and French President Nicolas Sarkozy. They discussed the situation in the eurozone and agreed that decisive action is necessary to resolve the crisis and ensure economic recovery. The President will continue to coordinate with his European counterparts leading up to the EU Summit on October 23 and the G20 Summit on November 3-4. Additionally, President Obama and President Sarkozy briefly discussed the need for the parties involved to return to the negotiating table for Middle East peace issues. Lastly, President Obama congratulated Prime Minister Cameron on his 45th birthday.